Sounds reasonable.

I didn't want to wait, so I changed my copy of FvwmEvent.

I then went on to do this:

#*FvwmAudioPlayCmd audioplay
#*FvwmAudioDir /opt/sounds
*FvwmAudioCmd "Exec cd /opt/sounds;audioplay"
AddToMenu "Module-Popup" "FvwmEvent - Audio" FvwmEvent FvwmAudio

This worked, but   I question  if  the  need  for  quotes  around  the
"*FvwmAudioCmd" is  the behavior you intended.   I don't see it in the
man page.  (It may be implied,  but I didn't pick  it up.) The problem
is  that  when the command   is  parsed,  its   parsed by  a  call  to
GetArgument().  This  pulls one token out  of the "*FvwmAudioCmd" line
null terminates it and uses it as the command, the rest of the line is
ignored.

