I haven't looked at the patch, but I don't like the idea of new patches
being applied so late in the game.  If Brady and others like the
changes, maybe the code can be integrated into the development tree.

In the meantime, you're right that there is a bug in the isgraph() --
some vendor-supplied isgraph() functions just do an indexed lookup off
the passed in argument, and will segfault (linux's doesn't have this
problem).  My working version has this fixed -- just add:

isascii(keysym) &&

before each call to isgraph(keysym) (there are three, all in menus.c).

Brady, this is essential to do before release-- it is a bug with an easy 
fix.

