I agree 5,000%!  :)

We simply _MUST_ get a new version of fvwm2 out.  Fvwm2 has never
actually had an "official" release, just betas, that's why so many
people are still using (and vendors still shipping) Fvwm1.

As I've said here before, lengthy release cycles are very vicious.  We
have to get the "first" release done, and all work should be geared
towards attaining that goal as quickly as possible.  In the past we've
never gotten to "release" point for precisely this reason: it takes long
enough that someone has a "must have" change, then there's a round of
bugfixing, etc. and it just goes on and on.

A line must be drawn; at this point, major changes like this, no matter
how desirable, simply _MUST_ wait.  Hey, I'm giving up on getting
autoconf support for Fvwm 2.2, remember!  :)

All IMO, of course.

Hopefully when Jason gets back he can set up a CVS tree, then new
features can be integrated on a development branch.

