Hi There,
	I'm having problems due to the way that AnimatedMove moves the cursor
with the window.  Could this be stopped?

I have an FvwmButtons at the bottom of the screen and I run an FvwmAuto 
that moves the FvwmButtons up when the cursor enters and down when it
leaves (just like  the Windows95 taskbar).  The problem with
AnimatedMove moving the cursor is that when I move the cursor out of the
FvwmButtons the AnimatedMove fights with me as I move the cursor (it
wins).

I can see that it is desireable to move the cursor when a menu is being
moved aside to make room for a submenu but I think that the cursor
moving should be done by the menu-popping thing rather than the
AnimatedMove function it calls.  The menu-popping thing already moves
the cursor back so it shouldn't be impossible.

Cheers,
Tim.
