Took me a while to remember what that was (had to dig though the
patch).

I believe it's to make mouse button bindings take effect in proper
order.  Say you have the right mouse button bound to Lower on the
title bar (which I do) and you use ClickToFocus (which I also do).  If
you click the right mouse button on the title bar of a window that
doesn't have the focus, it gets the focus, RAISES it, *then* lowers
it.  I believe that after that patch is applied that the window will
just lower without raising (perhaps not getting the focus either).

Don't recall who submitted it, as I don't have a reference to it (that
I recognize anyways) in my notes of what I was attempting to get into
2.0.47 before I gave up.

