Check out our distribution available from:

http://web.mit.edu/mstachow/www/scwm.html

And start using scwm and reporting (and fixing) bugs!  We're pushing
forward on the documentation front (which is unfortunately a bit
sparse), and have a bunch of projects like the .fvwm2rc->.scwrmrc
translator, adding documentation, event-system rewrite, improved fvwm2
module support, native scheme module support, constraints-based window
positioning and sizing, loadable menu styles, loadable decoration
styles, and lots more.  After a contribution or two and an interest in
further development, we're very open about giving write access to the
CVS repository (bazaar-style! :-) ).  Maciej has done an excellent job
maintaining the distribution and using all the auto-tools to make
building scwm a virtual no-brainer (even with the complexities of using
recent guile snapshots).

Thanks for your interest... hopefully others will join in our excitement!

Greg

