Well, libguile already provides the Scheme interpreter, so it takes
basically no space in the program itself. libguile is a bit
heavyweight right now (adds 1M or so to program RSS), but there are
plans to separate out the core Scheme interpreter from it and make
everything else into loadable modules. That should be very small
indeed. In fact, by agressive separation of fvwm code into lodable
binary modules (which libguile supports portably already), it should
eventually be possible to achieve a smaller RSS than fvwm2 itself for
some configurations.

