Well, we're down to 60% overhead or so in some cases, and this is
again _before_ the _huge_ amounts of work that will go into reducing
the memory footprint before this is considered an end-user ready
product.

> Don't forget my prior point  about the conversion  script.  I have  my
> doubts that  a fully  functional fvwm2 to  Scwm converter  is going to
