like a zealot?

If you keep this up, "small-is-beautiful" will lose a credible
defender, which would be a shame.  Somebody's got to keep Greg and
Maciej on their toes about the economy and footprint issues.  I was
expecting it would be you, but you're sabotaging your own arguments
rather effectively by flaming and making these peevish threats to 
start a hostile fork.

> I wonder if Eric would like people on fetchmail-friends insisting that
> mail-getter was better and that people still working on fetchmail were
> wasting their time.  Perhaps fetchmail needs to have a guile interpreter
> built in.

Fetchmail doesn't have Guile because fetchmail doesn't need Guile.  As
presently designed, fetchmail is just a keep-it-simple-stupid mail
transport agent.

If fetchmail were going to do content-based filtering or something
else that suggested it needed a Turing-complete language, I'd bolt
Guile onto fetchmail in about a nanosecond.

When you get down to it, POP and IMAP just aren't very complicated.
Because this is true, fetchmail can be both right and *simple*.  The
semantic domain of window-manager configurations, OTOH, is much, much
richer; enough so to suggest such a language.

BTW, if you'd like to join fetchmail-friends and trash my design, feel free.
I'm sure the response from the regulars there would be, hm, well,
"entertaining" is the word that occurred to me second.
