Termcap is needed by some versions of Guile. It's only really needed
if Guile is built to use readline, and if not, it shouldn't even get
paged in.

> For comparison, 2.0.47d with a single patch for fixed-size icons that
> Ian Speilman gave up getting into the tree, so which I now patch myself:
> 
> -rwxr-xr-x   1 root     system     176632 Jul 16 11:51 /usr/bin/X11/fvwm2
> 
> So the savings is about 6k.... before you start snarfing in 370k shared
> libs.  (At least termcap is almost always loaded by something else.)
> The scwm build was stock, both executables are stripped.
> 
> Considering you and Eric (and Brady?!) have decided that all the config
> loading code was complicated bloat and that huge savings would occur by
> removing it, you'd think it would show up in the size of the executable
> to have so much less code.   But it doesn't.
> 
> It's the same size plus a 370k library.
> 


Note that scwm has had _many_ extra primitives for quite some time
that provide extra features that fvwm does not. Before we added those,
scwm was about 2/3 the size of fvwm in compiled code.

Both these extra primitives and many of the old fvwm builtins will be
moved out of the core once we have our loadable module infrastructure
going, which should be easy - Guile provides near-transparent support
for that.


