OK folks, here's my take on this:

Lets get Fvwm2 out first.

Then we can each figure out wether to go with Fvwm or Scwm.  I don't
think Scwm should be renamed Fvwm3 it's just going to be too different. 
>From my perspective the config language is the main feature of a window
manager after all most of them can cope with moving and iconifying
windows, their strengths and weaknesses lie in the users ability to
control the way in which their windows work.  I moved to fvwm from
mwm/dtwm because I couldn't get them to manage the focus in the way I
wanted.  Fvwm is better but not exactly what I want. What I really want
is to be able is to be able to write high level code that can get at the
window manager's state and window lists.  I'll probably move to scwm
when I get the time.

Cheers,
Tim.
