I've got a problem with iconifying windows using a mouse button that
doesn't happen with a key press.

I bind mouse button 3 on the border to the function my_iconify and I
bind the keypad_decimal key to the same function:

Key KP_Decimal WTSF N my_iconify
Mouse 3 TSF A my_resizeiconify

AddToFunc my_resizeiconify
+			"M" Resize
+			"C" my_iconify

AddToFunc my_iconify	"I" Iconify 1
+			"I" my_prev

AddToFunc my_prev	"I" Prev [!Iconic CurrentDesk] my_focus
+			"I" None [!Iconic CurrentDesk] my_previcon

AddToFunc my_previcon	"I" Prev [Iconic CurrentDesk] my_focus
+			"I" None [Iconic CurrentDesk] my_home

my_home warps the cursor into an FvwmButtons and my_focus raises and
focuses to the selected window.

What all this is supposed to achieve is that when I iconify a window the
focus moves to the previous window in the stack or to an icon if there
are no windows open (and the FvwmButtons if there are no icons).

This works fine from the key binding but with the mouse binding
something goes awry with the ordering of events.  The last window on a
desk cannot be iconified (well, it looks like it gets iconified and then
my_prev finds that window and runs my_focus which deiconifies it) and
sometimes whene ther are more than one window on the screen the wrong
window gets iconified (very annoying).  It feels like the first line of
my_prev is finding the last uniconified window on the screen and
focusing to it even though my_iconify has just iconified it.  The weird
thing is that it only fails if a mouse button is used.  The iconifying
of the wrong window might be related to the "Prev ... my_focus" moving
the focus before the Iconify 1 takes effect so it probably is one bug

Any ideas what changed between 2.0.46 and 2.0.47d that might be
involved?

Cheers,
Tim.
