made no difference.  There really does seem to be a problem with Iconify
followed by Prev in which the Prev finds the iconified window even
though it shouldn't.  I expanded the functions to give the following
test:

AddToFunc my_resizeiconify "C" Current [!FvwmButtons] Iconify 1
+ "C" Prev [!Iconic CurrentDesk] Focus
+ "C" Prev [!Iconic CurrentDesk] Raise
+ "C" None [!Iconic CurrentDesk] Prev [Iconic CurrentDesk] Focus
+ "C" None [!Iconic CurrentDesk] Prev [Iconic CurrentDesk] Raise
+ "C" None [!Iconic CurrentDesk] None [Iconic CurrentDesk] Next
[FvwmButtons CirculateHit] Focus

When there is more than one window on the current desk this works fine. 
Lines 2 & 3 get executed and the focus moves. When there is just one
non-iconic window on the current desk lines 2 & 3 should get skipped and
lines 4, 5 & 6 should get executed.  This doesn't happen, instead the
focus is set to the window which was just iconified.  I don't know
wether the iconification happens or not, it is too fast.

The weird thing is that if the above function is called from a keypress
(with the "C"'s replaced with "I"'s) it works fine.  If called from a
mouse button with "I"'s instead of "C"'s the iconification happens but
the focus doesn't get moved.

